Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve and peel @shallot{1}, then thinly slice lengthwise. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{10%ounce}. Zest 1 TBSP zest from @lemon{1}, then halve. Tear @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into small pieces or grate on large holes of a #grater{}. Finely chop @chives{¼%ounce}.

Put @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup} and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}. Place over medium-high heat. Toast, stirring, until deep golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Pat @chicken breasts{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add chicken to same pan and cook until done, ~{5-8%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest on a #plate{}. Set pan aside. Place shallot and 1 packet @garlic herb butter{4%tablespoon} in a second large pan. Heat over medium-high heat. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Pour in @milk{6.75%ounce} and 1 @chicken stock concentrate{2}. Bring to a simmer.

Whisk @Italian cheese blend{1%cup} and mozzarella cheeses into pan with milk. Stir in juice from one lemon half. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Adjust heat to low. Meanwhile, add @spinach and artichoke ravioli{18%ounce} to pot of water, lower heat, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until al dente, ~{2-4%minutes}. Reserve 1 1/2 cups cooking water, then drain. Stir ravioli, tomatoes, @peas{4%ounce}, and ¾ cup cooking water into sauce in pan. Simmer until just thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add more cooking water as needed to loosen pasta sauce. Set aside. Place @thyme{¼%ounce} sprigs, ½ cup water, and remaining chicken stock concentrate in pan used for chicken and bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Pour in any juices released by chicken. Let reduce slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reduce heat to low and stir in remaining garlic herb butter and juice from other lemon half. Season with salt and pepper. Discard thyme sprigs.

Thinly slice chicken on a slight diagonal and arrange on a #serving platter{}. Spoon pan sauce over chicken; sprinkle with half the chives. Arrange pasta on another #platter{} and sprinkle with panko, @Parmesan cheese{½%cup}, lemon zest, remaining chives, and @?chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste (or serve on the side). Serve family style.

> This dinner can be served with a side of crusty bread to soak up the delicious sauce.